{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|くつ}}

{{IPAchar|/kutu/}} → {{IPAchar|/kut͡su/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=くつ|-}}, ultimately from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*kutuy}}. Appears in compound terms listed in the ''{{w|Wamyō Ruijushō}}'' of 938 CE.

The ancient combining form of modern reading ''kuchi''.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> Likely the original form.

No longer productive in modern Japanese. Only found in older compounds.

There are interesting potential phonetic and semantic overlaps with {{cog|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|窟|hole; cave}}, {{ltc-l|口|mouth; opening; hole}}; {{cog|ko|굳}}, {{m|ko|굿||hole; hollow; cavity}}; possibly even {{cog|ain|クㇳ|tr=kut}}, {{m|ain|クッチ|tr=kutchi||throat}}. One possibility is that these represent prehistoric nativized borrowings from Chinese. However, there is yet no clear evidence of relatedness.

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|口%号|くつ%うた}}: an [[improvised]] [[poem]] or [[song]]
* {{ja-r|口%籠|くつ%こ}}: a [[muzzle]]
* {{ja-r|鼾|くつち|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|癲|くつち|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|癲癇|くつち}}: [[snoring]]; [[epilepsy]]
* {{ja-r|轡|くつばみ|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|銜|くつばみ|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|勒|くつばみ}}: a [[bit]] {{qualifier|as for a horse's mouth}}
* {{ja-r|口%巻|くつ%まき}}: the [[winding]] holding an [[arrowhead]] to the [[shaft]] of an [[arrow]]
* {{ja-r|轡|くつわ|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|馬銜|くつわ}}: a [[bit]] {{qualifier|as for a horse's mouth}}
{{der-bottom}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|くち}}

&#42;{{IPAchar|/kutu i/}} → {{IPAchar|/kuti/}} → {{IPAchar|/kut͡ɕi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}, ultimately from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*kutuy}}. Appears in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.<ref name="MYS">{{RQ:Manyoshu|14|3532}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man14Yo.html#3532 here]</ref>

Shift from ''kutu'' above, probably by fusion with ancient nominal particle {{ja-r|い}}. Compare the phonetic development of {{m|ja|神|tr=kami||spirit, god}} from ''kamu'' + ''i'', {{m|ja|木|tr=ki||tree}} from ''ko'' + ''i'', {{m|ja|目|tr=me||eye}} from ''ma'' + ''i''.

